## Phase 2c Summary — FIND-408 Store Write Surface Narrowing

### Change Applied

FIND-408: appShellStore write surface narrowed.

Before (sprint-2):
  export const appShellStore = {
    subscribe: _store.subscribe,
    set: _store.set,       // exposed — could be called from anywhere
    update: _store.update, // exposed — could be called from anywhere
  };

After (sprint-3):
  export const appShellStore: { subscribe: typeof _store.subscribe } = {
    subscribe: _store.subscribe,
    // set and update intentionally omitted (FIND-408 / REQ-021)
  };

All writes now MUST go through setAppShellState(). This is enforced at two
levels:
  1. Type level: appShellStore.set does not exist; TypeScript errors on use.
  2. Static audit level: PROP-011 audit catches setAppShellState() calls from
     files outside ALLOWED_WRITERS set.

Test update: effectful-isolation.test.ts REQ-021 test updated to assert that
"set" and "update" are NOT in the public appShellStore object, confirming the
structural constraint.

